{"key":"post-19559233","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19559233</id>\n<content>A few years ago I had the bright idea to do some large commercial straw grows(oyster) with perforated pvc pipe buried through the substrates for aeration.&amp;nbsp; The idea was for air flow to prevent stagnation, and the pipes could be switched over to water to hydrate from within by changing valve position.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Unfortunately, the holes provided the perfect environment for molds to develop, and it was a massive fail.&amp;nbsp; Live and learn.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19564228</next>\n<prev>19559189</prev>\n<first>19551930</first>\n<last>19564754</last>\n<when>1392263953</when>\n<utime>02/13/14 05:59 AM</utime>\n</post>"}